  <h2>Retention Requirements</h2>

  <!-- Justified paragraph -->
  <p class="justify">
    Students must maintain academic standards in order to continue in the 
    Creative Technologies program. GPA requirements vary depending on 
    the chosen sequence and must be maintained throughout enrollment.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Audio and Music Production and Interdisciplinary Technologies</strong> –
      Maintain an overall cumulative GPA of 2.50.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Game Design</strong> – Maintain a 2.50 cumulative GPA overall 
      and 3.0 within the major. Consecutive Fall–Spring enrollment required 
      during final year.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Standards for Progress</h2>

  <!-- Centered paragraph -->
  <p class="center">
    Students must demonstrate competency through an intermediate portfolio review
    and maintain a cumulative GPA of 2.50.
  </p>

  <h3>Sequences in Creative Technologies</h3>

  <p>
    Students may pursue specialized study in Audio Production, Game Design,
    or Interdisciplinary Technologies depending on academic goals and interests.
  </p>

